{"abstract": "Appeals courts have ruled that it is not unusual for parties to conceal their true goals. In other words, no one tells the truth when negotiating a deal.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/19/business/dealbook/when-lies-are-allowed-in-a-business-deal.html", "snippet": "Appeals courts have ruled that it is not unusual for parties to conceal their true goals. In other words, no one tells the truth when negotiating a deal.", "lead_paragraph": "The French philosopher Ren\u00e9 Descartes wrote that \u201call deception or fraud involves some imperfection.\u201d How much imperfection is required to be convicted of the federal crimes of mail and wire fraud has been clarified, at least a little bit, by recent appeals court decisions recognizing that some lying is acceptable, and even expected, in the business world.", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/04/19/business/db-whitecollar1/db-whitecollar1-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 973, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/04/19/business/db-whitecollar1/db-whitecollar1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 973}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/04/19/business/db-whitecollar1/db-whitecollar1-jumbo.jpg", "height": 1024, "width": 632, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/04/19/business/db-whitecollar1/db-whitecollar1-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 2048, "width": 1264, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2016/04/19/business/db-whitecollar1/db-whitecollar1-thumbStandard.jpg", "height": 75, "width": 75,